article.headline: Siena 60, Canisius 50
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- O.D. Anosike had a double-double with 15 points and 11 rebounds as Siena snapped a four-game losing streak with a 60-50 win over Canisius on Saturday. The win also snapped the Saints' 10-game road losing streak against Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference teams. Kyle Downey also scored 15 points, Evan Hymes added 12 and Brandon Walters grabbed 10 rebounds for the Saints (11-14, 6-9), who allowed a season-low in points. Siena went on a 12-0 run in a 6:38 span that covered the end of the first half and the beginning of the second to open up a 41-26 lead. A basket by Hymes capped the run with 16:41 remaining. The Saints built a 19-point lead before Canisius scored the final nine points of the game. Harold Washington scored 16 points and Gaby Belardo added 13 for the Golden Griffins (4-21, 1-13), who have lost nine in a row.
